{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"User notification preferences use opt-in defaults with per-category email subscriptions and optional PreferencesService injection into NotificationService","detail":"Design choices: (1) Opt-in by default — users with no preferences record receive all notifications, ensuring backwards compatibility and no disruption. (2) PreferencesService is injected into NotificationService via setPreferencesService() rather than a constructor dependency, keeping existing code and tests working without modification. (3) Preferences are checked in NotificationService.dispatch() before creating the payload, so suppressed notifications never reach adapters. (4) Repository pattern matches existing codebase conventions (BaseRepository subclass). (5) EmailFrequency type (immediate/daily_digest/weekly_digest) is modeled but only 'immediate' is actively used — digest batching is a future concern. (6) Per-category subscription uses NotificationType directly, avoiding a separate mapping layer.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/services/preferences.service.ts","agent_id":"main","id":"01KN136P47573F0VYG48EMBF3W","timestamp":"2026-03-31T04:42:34.503Z"}
